reviewText:
Pros: Fun game, with great graphics and an acceptable combat system;
Lots of loot.

Cons: Gets old too fast;
Not recommended for AMD users, as the game crashes constantly in chapter 8/Final Chapter.

I love this game!

Too much problems with connection in multiplayer.
And that is only con there is to me. ^^;

TL:DR: No matter how good you think this game is, DO NOT BUY THIIS UNSUPPORTED AND BUG-RIDDEN SOFTWARE

While this game offers compelling action gameplay, character building and 3-player co-op, the bugs will suck your will to play it. I have spent a similar amount of time troubleshooting the game as I have playing it.

I have played this game in local co-op mode (3 players, LAN) and we have had:
- game not running after install;
- multiple re-installs;
- blank screen at Mount Gundabad;
- one player being constantly kicked out of the party at Rivendell;
- at least one player per session being randomly kicked from the hosted match;
- Other small performance, inventory, graphical, sound and quality of life bugs.

Running the game across 3 laptops, 1 Windows 7 and 2 Windows 8.1. No superfluous software running in the background and all video drivers were current and windows updatd to current.

This game would only be suitable for someone who is a single-player masochist who is willing to either run with multiple saves and/or unintended means to get over the bugs. A shame, as it is a good concept poorly executed and now consigned to abandonware.
